annotationA: Paramyosin, long form; Paramyosin is a muscle protein found only in invertebrates. It dimerizes into a coiled-coil that occupies the interior of the thick filament. Its role is thought to be structural, although it can be phosphorylated and this is important for muscle function
annotationB: Myosin light chain alkali; Calcium ion binding; microfilament motor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: mesoderm development; muscle contraction
